<section class="panel">
  <h1>Fuel Cost Estimator</h1>
  <p class="muted">
    Use this to estimate trip fuel spend before dispatch. Enter miles, truck MPG, and local diesel price per gallon to get
    gallons used, total cost, and cost per mile.
  </p>

  <% if (errors.length) { %>
    <div class="alert error">
      <ul>
      <% errors.forEach((error) => { %>
        <li><%= error %></li>
      <% }) %>
      </ul>
    </div>
  <% } %>

  <form class="stack" method="post" action="/tools/fuel-cost">
    <label>Miles
      <input type="number" step="0.01" min="0.01" name="miles" value="<%= formData.miles %>" required />
    </label>
    <label>MPG
      <input type="number" step="0.01" min="0.01" name="mpg" value="<%= formData.mpg %>" required />
    </label>
    <label>Diesel Price ($/gallon)
      <input type="number" step="0.01" min="0.01" name="diesel_price" value="<%= formData.diesel_price %>" required />
    </label>
    <div class="row">
      <button class="btn" type="submit">Calculate</button>
      <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/tools/fuel-cost">Reset</a>
    </div>
  </form>
</section>

<% if (result) { %>
  <section class="card tool-result-card">
    <h2>Results</h2>
    <p><strong>Gallons Used:</strong> <%= result.gallons_used %> gal</p>
    <p><strong>Total Cost:</strong> $<%= result.total_cost %></p>
    <p><strong>Cost Per Mile:</strong> $<%= result.cost_per_mile %></p>
  </section>
<% } %>

<section class="card">
  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <p><strong>How accurate is this?</strong><br />It is a planning estimate. Real fuel burn changes with load, speed, weather, and idle time.</p>
  <p><strong>Should I use average MPG or last trip MPG?</strong><br />Use your recent real-world average MPG for the truck and load profile.</p>
  <p><strong>Why does cost per mile matter?</strong><br />It helps compare lanes and decide whether a rate still makes sense after fuel.</p>
  <p><strong>Can I use this for partial routes?</strong><br />Yes, enter only the miles for that route segment.</p>
</section>
